1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,890
Four ways to develop the Big Thinker's vocabulary.

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:08,689
Here are four ways to help you develop a Big Thinker's vocabulary.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:09,730
One.

4
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:15,330
Use big, positive, cheerful words and phrases to describe how you feel.

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,449
When someone asks, how do you feel today?

6
00:00:18,449 --> 00:00:23,650
And you respond with an, I'm tired, I have a headache, I wish it were Saturday,

7
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,090
I don't feel so good.

8
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:27,890
You actually make yourself feel worse.

9
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,330
Practice this.

10
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:33,010
It's a very simple point, but it has tremendous power.

11
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:38,049
Every time someone asks you, how are you, or how are you feeling today,

12
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:44,770
respond with a, just wonderful, thanks, and you, or say, great, or fine.

13
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:52,449
Say you feel wonderful at every possible opportunity, and you will begin to feel wonderful, and bigger, too.

14
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:56,130
Become known as a person who always feels great.

15
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:57,809
It wins friends.

16
00:00:57,809 --> 00:00:59,409
2.

17
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:04,850
Use bright, cheerful, favorable words and phrases to describe other people.

18
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:10,210
Make it a rule to have a big, positive word for all your friends and associates.

19
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:18,130
When you and someone else are discussing an absent third party, be sure you compliment him with big words and phrases like,

20
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:20,049
he's really a fine fellow.

21
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,770
They tell me he's working out wonderfully well.

22
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:27,250
Be extremely careful to avoid the petty cut him down language.

23
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:34,130
Sooner or later, third parties hear what's been said, and then such talk only cuts you down.

24
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:35,970
Three.

25
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:39,490
Use positive language to encourage others.

26
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,850
Compliment people personally at every opportunity.

27
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,650
Everyone you know craves praise.

28
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:49,730
Have a special good word for your wife or husband every day.

29
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:53,090
Notice and compliment the people who work with you.

30
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:57,169
Praise, sincerely administered, is a success tool.

31
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,130
Use it.

32
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:01,010
Use it again and again and again.

33
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:06,450
Compliment people on their appearance, their work, their achievements, their families.

34
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:12,450
Four, use positive words to outline plans to others.

35
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:18,770
When people hear something like this, here is some good news, we face a genuine opportunity,

36
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,250
their minds start to sparkle.

37
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:26,289
But when they hear something like, whether we like it or not, we've got a job to do.

38
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:30,689
The mind movie is dull and boring, and they react accordingly.

39
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:33,809
Promise victory and watch eyes light up.

40
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:36,289
Promise victory and win support.

41
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:39,650
Build castles, don't dig graves.

42
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,770
See what can be, not just what is.

